Dow's 50-point drop led by losses in shares of Verizon Communications Inc., Dow Inc.

The Dow Jones Industrial Average is falling Friday morning with shares of Verizon Communications Inc. and Dow Inc. seeing the biggest losses for the price-weighted average. The Dow DJIA, -2.29% was most recently trading 50 points, or 0.2%, lower, as shares of Verizon Communications Inc. VZ, -0.25% and Dow Inc. DOW, -2.84% are contributing to the blue-chip gauge's intraday decline. Verizon Communications Inc.'s shares are down $0.85, or 1.4%, while those of Dow Inc. have dropped $0.70, or 1.3%, combining for a roughly 11-point drag on the Dow. Other components contributing significantly to the decline include Pfizer PFE, -0.68%, JPMorgan Chase JPM, -2.47%, and Walgreens Boots WBA, -2.18%. A $1 move in any one of the 30 components of the index results in a 6.78-point swing.